1// Copyright (c) 2011-present, Facebook, Inc. All rights reserved.
2// This source code is licensed under both the GPLv2 (found in the
3// COPYING file in the root directory) and Apache 2.0 License
4// (found in the LICENSE.Apache file in the root directory).
5
6/* Copyright (c) 2011 The LevelDB Authors. All rights reserved.
7 Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
8 found in the LICENSE file. See the AUTHORS file for names of contributors.
9
10 C bindings for rocksdb. May be useful as a stable ABI that can be
11 used by programs that keep rocksdb in a shared library, or for
12 a JNI api.
13
14 Does not support:
15 . getters for the option types
16 . custom comparators that implement key shortening
17 . capturing post-write-snapshot
18 . custom iter, db, env, cache implementations using just the C bindings
19
20 Some conventions:
21
22 (1) We expose just opaque struct pointers and functions to clients.
23 This allows us to change internal representations without having to
24 recompile clients.
25
26 (2) For simplicity, there is no equivalent to the Slice type. Instead,
27 the caller has to pass the pointer and length as separate
28 arguments.
29
30 (3) Errors are represented by a null-terminated c string. NULL
31 means no error. All operations that can raise an error are passed
32 a "char** errptr" as the last argument. One of the following must
33 be true on entry:
34 *errptr == NULL
35 *errptr points to a malloc()ed null-terminated error message
36 On success, a leveldb routine leaves *errptr unchanged.
37 On failure, leveldb frees the old value of *errptr and
38 set *errptr to a malloc()ed error message.
39
40 (4) Bools have the type unsigned char (0 == false; rest == true)
41
42 (5) All of the pointer arguments must be non-NULL.
43*/
44
45#pragma once
46

48#ifdef ROCKSDB_DLL
49#ifdef ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_EXPORTS
50#define ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API __declspec(dllexport)
51#else
52#define ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API __declspec(dllimport)
53#endif
54#else
55#define ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API
56#endif
57#else
58#define ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API
59#endif
60

63#endif

515// if values_list[i] == NULL and errs[i] == NULL,
516// then we got status.IsNotFound(), which we will not return.
517// all errors except status status.ok() and status.IsNotFound() are returned.
518//
519// errs, values_list and values_list_sizes must be num_keys in length,
520// allocated by the caller.
521// errs is a list of strings as opposed to the conventional one error,
522// where errs[i] is the status for retrieval of keys_list[i].
523// each non-NULL errs entry is a malloc()ed, null terminated string.
524// each non-NULL values_list entry is a malloc()ed array, with
525// the length for each stored in values_list_sizes[i].
526extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_multi_get(
527 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options, size_t num_keys,
528 const char* const* keys_list, const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
529 char** values_list, size_t* values_list_sizes, char** errs);
530
531extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_multi_get_with_ts(
532 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options, size_t num_keys,
533 const char* const* keys_list, const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
534 char** values_list, size_t* values_list_sizes, char** timestamp_list,
535 size_t* timestamp_list_sizes, char** errs);
536
537extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_multi_get_cf(
538 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
539 const rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* const* column_families,
540 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
541 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, char** values_list,
542 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** errs);
543
544extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_multi_get_cf_with_ts(
545 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
546 const rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* const* column_families,
547 size_t num_keys, const char* const* keys_list,
548 const size_t* keys_list_sizes, char** values_list,
549 size_t* values_list_sizes, char** timestamps_list,
550 size_t* timestamps_list_sizes, char** errs);
551
552// The MultiGet API that improves performance by batching operations
553// in the read path for greater efficiency. Currently, only the block based
554// table format with full filters are supported. Other table formats such
555// as plain table, block based table with block based filters and
556// partitioned indexes will still work, but will not get any performance
557// benefits.
558//
559// Note that all the keys passed to this API are restricted to a single
560// column family.
561//
562// Parameters -
563// db - the RocksDB instance.
564// options - ReadOptions
565// column_family - ColumnFamilyHandle* that the keys belong to. All the keys
566// passed to the API are restricted to a single column family
567// num_keys - Number of keys to lookup
568// keys_list - Pointer to C style array of keys with num_keys elements
569// keys_list_sizes - Pointer to C style array of the size of corresponding key
570// in key_list with num_keys elements.
571// values - Pointer to C style array of PinnableSlices with num_keys elements
572// statuses - Pointer to C style array of Status with num_keys elements
573// sorted_input - If true, it means the input keys are already sorted by key
574// order, so the MultiGet() API doesn't have to sort them
575// again. If false, the keys will be copied and sorted
576// internally by the API - the input array will not be
577// modified
578extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_batched_multi_get_cf(
579 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options,
580 rocksdb_column_family_handle_t* column_family, size_t num_keys,
581 const char* const* keys_list, const size_t* keys_list_sizes,
582 rocksdb_pinnableslice_t** values, char** errs, const bool sorted_input);
583
584// The value is only allocated (using malloc) and returned if it is found and
585// value_found isn't NULL. In that case the user is responsible for freeing it.
586extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API unsigned char rocksdb_key_may_exist(
587 rocksdb_t* db, const rocksdb_readoptions_t* options, const char* key,
588 size_t key_len, char** value, size_t* val_len, const char* timestamp,
589 size_t timestamp_len, unsigned char* value_found);
590
591// The value is only allocated (using malloc) and returned if it is found and

593extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API unsigned char rocksdb_key_may_exist_cf(

1011/* Options utils */
1012
1013// Load the latest rocksdb options from the specified db_path.
1014//
1015// On success, num_column_families will be updated with a non-zero
1016// number indicating the number of column families.
1017// The returned db_options, column_family_names, and column_family_options
1018// should be released via rocksdb_load_latest_options_destroy().
1019//
1020// On error, a non-null errptr that includes the error message will be
1021// returned. db_options, column_family_names, and column_family_options
1022// will be set to NULL.
1023extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_load_latest_options(
1024 const char* db_path, rocksdb_env_t* env, bool ignore_unknown_options,
1025 rocksdb_cache_t* cache, rocksdb_options_t** db_options,
1026 size_t* num_column_families, char*** column_family_names,
1027 rocksdb_options_t*** column_family_options, char** errptr);
1028
1029extern ROCKSDB_LIBRARY_API void rocksdb_load_latest_options_destroy(
1030 rocksdb_options_t* db_options, char** list_column_family_names,
1031 rocksdb_options_t** list_column_family_options, size_t len);
